1 0 0 1 72 710 Tm
(? run_pipeline.py: single entry-point script for the full workflow) Tj
T*
(? run_sim.py: standalone simulation entry point) Tj
T*
(? spec_parser.py: structured behavior extraction) Tj
T*
(? tb_generator.py: Verilog testbench generation) Tj
T*
(? simulator.py: iverilog / vvp execution and result collection) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The agent loop is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(specification.md + mutant_*.v) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(   parse behavior) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(   generate test plan) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(   generate testbench) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(      simulate) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(   analyze results) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
( refine if needed) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This differs from one-shot prompting because the system preserves intermediate artifacts,) Tj
T*
(invokes external tools, reads execution results, and can improve later outputs based on) Tj
T*
(failures.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. TOOLS & FRAMEWORKS \(EDA TOOLS, LLMS, AGENT FRAMEWORKS\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Tools used:) Tj
T*
(? Codex CLI: model execution interface) Tj
T*
(? gpt-5-codex: specification parsing, test-plan generation, and testbench generation) Tj
T*
(? iverilog: Verilog compilation) Tj
T*
(? vvp: simulation execution) Tj
T*
(? Python scripts: orchestration and result processing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(We do not use a separate external agent framework. The agent logic is implemented directly) Tj
T*
(in Python as an explicit planner-executor-feedback loop.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. CONTEXT ENGINEERING \(INPUTS, REPRESENTATION, CONTEXT MANAGEMENT\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The agent receives:) Tj
T*
(? raw specification text) Tj
T*
(? candidate RTL implementations) Tj
T*
(? recovered module header information) Tj
T*
(? simulation feedback from prior iterations) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The context is represented as:) Tj
T*
(? raw text for the original specification) Tj
T*
(? structured JSON for parsed behavior) Tj
T*
(? structured JSON for the generated test plan) Tj
T*
(? JSON logs and score summaries for simulation results) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(To control context size, parsed behavior and test plans are summarized before being reused) Tj
T*
(in large prompts. This reduced Codex timeouts and kept generation requests manageable.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
