() Tj
T*
(5. INTERACTION WITH EDA TOOLS \(INVOCATION, PARSING, ITERATION\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The agent uses Python subprocess calls to invoke:) Tj
T*
(? iverilog -g2012 to compile the generated testbench with each mutant RTL file) Tj
T*
(? vvp to execute the simulation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Simulation output is parsed using explicit PASS and FAIL markers. Results are stored as JSON) Tj
T*
(under artifacts/. This tool interaction is part of an iterative loop: if the score is weak) Tj
T*
(or the generated testbench fails, the agent can revise the next attempt.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. PROTOTYPE IMPLEMENTATION \(WHAT WORKS / INCOMPLETE PARTS\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Currently functional:) Tj
T*
(? natural-language specification parsing) Tj
T*
(? structured spec and test-plan artifact generation) Tj
T*
(? self-checking Verilog testbench generation) Tj
T*
(? automated simulation across all candidates in a problem directory) Tj
T*
(? score computation and JSON result reporting) Tj
T*
(? single-command execution via run_pipeline.py) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Still incomplete:) Tj
T*
(? full visible-benchmark evaluation) Tj
T*
(? systematic baseline comparison) Tj
T*
(? stronger robustness on more complex vectorized modules) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. INITIAL RESULTS \(>=1 TESTCASE, METRICS, BASELINE IF AVAILABLE\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(We evaluated the prototype on three real visible problems from the public ICLAD Google) Tj
T*
(Verification benchmark, using one iteration per problem.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Problem | Mutants | Passing Implementations | Compile Errors | Runtime \(s\) | Observation |) Tj
T*
(|--------|--------:|------------------------:|---------------:|------------:|-------------|) Tj
T*
(| enc_bin2gray | 31 | 1 | 0 | 62.6 | Strong discrimination |) Tj
T*
(| enc_bin2onehot | 31 | 1 | 0 | 141.8 | Strong discrimination |) Tj
T*
(| shift_right | 31 | 0 | 31 | 234.4 | Generated testbench failed to compile |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The first two results show that the agent can reduce 31 candidate implementations to a) Tj
T*
(single passing design in one iteration. The shift_right failure exposes a real limitation:) Tj
T*
(the generated testbench used variable part-select expressions that iverilog rejected.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(We also verified the packaged sample_problem, where the agent achieves 1/6 passing with no) Tj
T*
(compile errors.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8. AI USAGE & INSIGHTS \(CRITICAL\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(AI is central in three places:) Tj
T*
(? extracting structured hardware behavior from English specifications) Tj
T*
(? generating structured test plans) Tj
T*
(? generating and refining Verilog testbenches) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Where AI works well:) Tj
T*
(? interpreting ambiguous natural-language behavior) Tj
T*
(? proposing useful directed and corner-case tests) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
